There’s something irresistible about freshly baked breadsticks. Crispy on the outside, soft on the inside, and bursting with flavor, they make the perfect snack for any occasion. Whether you’re hosting a party, preparing an appetizer for a family dinner, or just looking for a quick homemade treat, breadsticks are an easy and delicious option. The best part? You can customize them with different seasonings, dips, and textures. Here are some easy homemade breadstick recipes that will make your snack time extra special.
Classic Garlic Parmesan Breadsticks
A timeless favorite, these garlic parmesan breadsticks are buttery, garlicky, and topped with delicious parmesan cheese.
Ingredients:
2 1/4 teaspoons (1 packet) active dry yeast
1 1/2 cups warm water
1 tablespoon sugar
1 teaspoon salt
3 1/2 cups all-purpose flour
3 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted
2 cloves garlic, minced
1/4 cup grated parmesan cheese
1 teaspoon dried oregano (optional)
Instructions:
In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water. Let it sit for 5–10 minutes until foamy.
Add salt and flour gradually, mixing until a soft dough forms.
Knead the dough for about 5 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Cover the dough and let it rise for 1 hour or until doubled in size.
Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Roll out the dough into a rectangle and cut into strips.
Twist each strip slightly and place on the prepared baking sheet.
Mix melted butter with minced garlic and brush it over the breadsticks.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake for 15–18 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with marinara sauce or garlic butter for dipping.
Cheesy Stuffed Breadsticks
For a gooey, cheesy delight, these stuffed breadsticks are a must-try.
Ingredients:
1 batch of prepared breadstick dough (use recipe above)
1 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
1/2 teaspoon dried basil
2 tablespoons melted butter
Instructions:
Roll out the dough into a large rectangle.
Cut into strips and place mozzarella cheese in the center of each strip.
Fold the dough over the cheese and seal the edges.
Twist slightly and place on a baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with garlic powder and basil.
Bake at 375°F for 15–18 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm with ranch or marinara sauce.
Sweet Cinnamon Sugar Breadsticks
For those with a sweet tooth, these cinnamon sugar breadsticks are the perfect treat.
Ingredients:
1 batch of prepared breadstick dough
2 tablespoons melted butter
1/4 cup sugar
1 teaspoon cinnamon
1/4 cup cream cheese icing (optional)
Instructions:
Roll out the dough and cut into strips.
Brush with melted butter.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle generously over the breadsticks.
Bake at 375°F for 15–18 minutes until golden brown.
Drizzle with cream cheese icing for extra sweetness.
Enjoy with coffee, tea, or hot chocolate.
Conclusion
Homemade breadsticks are easy to make and incredibly versatile. Whether you prefer savory or sweet, you can customize them to fit any occasion. With just a few simple ingredients and some creativity, you can turn basic dough into an irresistible snack. So why not give one of these recipes a try? Your taste buds will thank you!
